When you want to build a **large, maintainable Go application** (especially with multiple developers), structuring the code **properly** is key.

Go doesn't enforce structure, but there are **conventions and best practices** that almost all big Go projects follow â€” and that real companies use.

---

## ğŸ§­ Let's Walk Through the Standard Folder Structure

### âœ… Common Production-Grade Go Project Layout

```
your-app/
â”œâ”€â”€ cmd/                # Main application entry points
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ yourapp/        # This app's main.go (entry point)
â”‚       â””â”€â”€ main.go
â”œâ”€â”€ internal/           # Private app code (business logic, handlers)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ auth/           # Auth logic (signup/login, sessions, etc.)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ chat/           # Chat logic (websocket, rooms, messages)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ user/           # User handling (DB user model, lookups)
â”œâ”€â”€ pkg/                # Reusable packages (can be imported by others)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ utils/          # Utilities (hashing, time, validation)
â”œâ”€â”€ api/                # API layer, HTTP routing, handlers
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ http/           # HTTP handler functions
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ websocket/      # WebSocket upgrade, connections
â”œâ”€â”€ db/                 # Database schema, migrations, access layer
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ models/         # Structs + DB logic (e.g. GORM models)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ migrations/     # SQL migration files
â”œâ”€â”€ web/                # Frontend static files (HTML, CSS, JS)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ assets/         # Images, fonts, etc.
â”œâ”€â”€ config/             # Configuration loading (env, JSON, YAML)
â”œâ”€â”€ scripts/            # Bash scripts, test runners, etc.
â”œâ”€â”€ go.mod              # Module definition
â”œâ”€â”€ go.sum              # Dependency checksums
â””â”€â”€ README.md           # Project overview
```

---

## ğŸ” Key Folders Explained

| Folder      | Purpose                                                                                             |
| ----------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `cmd/`      | Entry point apps (like `main.go`) â€” great when you want multiple apps (e.g., CLI tool + web server) |
| `internal/` | Code that should **not be imported** from other modules â€” only your app                             |
| `pkg/`      | Reusable Go packages (could be shared with other teams/projects)                                    |
| `api/`      | All things HTTP and WebSocket routing/handlers                                                      |
| `db/`       | DB layer: models, migrations                                                                        |
| `web/`      | All static frontend files (HTML templates, JS, CSS)                                                 |
| `config/`   | Environment loading, config structs (Viper, dotenv, etc.)                                           |

---

## ğŸ›  Example: Where Things Will Go in Your Chat App

| Feature                | File/Folder                       |
| ---------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| `main.go`              | `cmd/yourapp/main.go`             |
| Sign up/Login handlers | `api/http/auth.go`                |
| WebSocket endpoint     | `api/websocket/chat.go`           |
| Chat room logic        | `internal/chat/room.go`           |
| User model             | `db/models/user.go`               |
| Message saving         | `db/models/message.go`            |
| Password hashing       | `pkg/utils/hash.go`               |
| DB connection          | `config/database.go`              |
| Frontend chat UI       | `web/index.html`, `web/chat.js`   |
| TLS certs (dev)        | `certs/cert.pem`, `certs/key.pem` |

---

## ğŸ“¦ Tools You Might Use

| Purpose               | Tool                                                              |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Dependency management | `go mod`                                                          |
| DB ORM                | [GORM](https://gorm.io/) or [`pgx`](https://github.com/jackc/pgx) |
| Web routing           | `Gin`, `Echo`, or `net/http`                                      |
| WebSocket             | `gorilla/websocket`                                               |
| Config                | `Viper`, or `.env` + `os.Getenv`                                  |
| Migrations            | `goose`, `golang-migrate`, or raw SQL                             |
| Static file serving   | `net/http.FileServer`                                             |

